snippet: Exactly where the three red-tailed hawks, found dead in or around Central Park, ingested the chemicals has not been determined.
abstract: Results of necropsies on three red-tailed hawks found in or just outside Central Park show that all three had rat poison in their systems when they died, but it is unknown where the chemicals were ingested; New York City Audubon official Glenn Phillips says most likely source is private rat-control programs in buildings that border most of the city's parks.
lead_paragraph: Exactly where the three red-tailed hawks, found dead in or around Central Park, ingested the chemicals has not been determined.

headline.seo: Rat Poison Is Found in Bodies of 3 Dead Hawks
